      • GetCompanyIdFromCoupon

        @GetMapping("/admin/coupons/companyId/{id}/{token}")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.Long> GetCompanyIdFromCoupon​(@PathVariable
                                                                                      long id,
                                                                                      @PathVariable
                                                                                      java.lang.String token)
                                                                               throws InvalidLoginException,
                                                                                      NoCompanyFoundException,
                                                                                      NoCouponFoundException
        That function will return the id of the company that associated to that coupon by the coupon id. For use in client side UX.
        Parameters:
        id - - the id of the coupon we want to get the company id of.
        token - - the token key to get the service from.
        Returns:
        the company id that listed to that coupon.
        Throws:
        InvalidLoginException - - if the token is invalid or expired.
        NoCompanyFoundException - - if the function not able to get any company from that id.
        NoCouponFoundException
